-- Swansea Beats West Ham 3-0 to Stay Unbeaten in Premier League
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-25T14:06:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-25/swansea-beats-west-ham-3-0-to-stay-unbeaten-in-premier-league.html
Miguel Michu scored his third goal
of the season as Swansea defeated West Ham 3-0 in English
soccer’s Premier League.  Angel Rangel and  Danny Graham  also scored in the Swans’
home win at the Liberty Stadium. Swansea has won its first two
games this season by a combined score of 8-0.  Rangel opened the scoring in the 20th minute with a shot
into the top left corner and Michu doubled the lead nine minutes
later. Graham then clinched the victory in the 64th minute with
shot from the center of the penalty area.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  